        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 4:16PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Peachtree Corners,
moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to exposed surfaces is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Duluth, Berkeley Lake, Norcross, Peachtree Corners, Mechanicsville,
Lilburn, Mountain Park, Alpharetta, Johns Creek, Doraville, Tucker,
Roswell, Dunwoody, and Sandy Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
